ing: 1 1/2 cups whole peeled tomatoes, drained and chopped
1 (4 ounce) can chopped green chile peppers
des: "A fondue dish is the perfect way to keep this thick, cheesy dip warm and melted. Corn, green chile peppers and tomato chunks make for a rich, spicy and satisfying accompaniment to tortilla chips."
ins: In a medium saucepan over medium heat, mix tomatoes, corn, milk and flour. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly, about 10 minutes. Gradually blend in Cheddar cheese and diced green chile peppers. Continue cooking until cheese has melted, about 10 minutes. Serve warm.
